      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You instantly teleport from your current location to any other spot within range, be that a place you visualize or simply by deciding a direction and distance. You can bring along objects as long as their weight doesn&rsquo;t exceed your maximum load. You leave behind an insubstantial image of yourself in your previous space until the end of your next turn. This image&rsquo;s features are too washed out to be mistaken for you, and it can&rsquo;t be harmed (though it can be dispelled). While it lasts, you can perceive the image&rsquo;s surroundings, flank nearby creatures, and target spells as if you still occupied its space.</span> </p>"
